title: Czech Republic Industrial Production
description: Industrial Production in Czech Republic increased 8.30 percent in September of 2022 over the same month in the previous year. Industrial Production in Czech Republic averaged 3.06 percent from 2001 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 55 percent in April of 2021 and a record low of -34.60 percent in April of 2020. In Czech Republic, industrial production measures the output of businesses integrated in industrial sector of the economy such as manufacturing, mining, and utilities. This page provides - Czech Republic Industrial Production - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Czech Statistical Office
